## The Process
**Worker startup:** before any task, read the project `CLAUDE.md` (L1) + this `CONTEXT.md` (L2) + your role
prompt `~/Developer/guide-setup/van-clief/templates/execution-workers/<role>.md` (the startup sequence, the
6-tier Preview-first tool tree, the JSON result contract). `~/Developer/guide-setup` is mounted **read-only** —
read the method (`…/van-clief/VAN-CLIEF-RULES.md`) + your role prompt there, **never edit the guide**.

Run by a **planning session** (sole assigner) + **worker sessions**. Work is **assigned, not grabbed** — each
task carries an `owner`. **The planner is the single writer of `planning/*.md`** — it moves the task into
`planning/progress.md` at dispatch (🔄 — owner · session · branch); the worker reads its assignment, then works in `branches/<slug>/` → PR → auto
independent review (reviewer subagent; escalates → `/code-review ultra` if large/risky/critical) → the human VERIFIES
the live feature → the worker merges to `main` in its own session (the planner never merges) → the entry **moves into `memory/completed-tasks.md`** (✅) → `/wrap` →
`/compact`. Production code reaches `main` only via merge. <project-specific workflow notes + gotchas…>

